    <bioghist id="aspace_1394e50dd9d3c19cd9824c4e9dd2bec2">
      <head>Historical Information</head>
      <p>This journal was maintained from 1853-1861 by an unidentified slave overseer - possibly
        Erastus Bishop of Petersburg, Virginia.</p>
    </bioghist>
    <scopecontent id="aspace_fe4be43d760f0f03355c39017b662da7">
      <head>Scope and Content</head>
      <p>The journal lists slave names and amount of crops (including cotton, peas, corn) each
        picked. It also lists when and which slaves were sick each day, how much money was obtained
        for a crop, home remedies for common illnesses, and the journey itinerary for a cargo
        ship.</p>
    </scopecontent>
